1. `MainActivity` will implement the `Pigeon.ImageHostApi` interface.
2. The `getSharedImages()` method in this implementation will retrieve the `receivedImageUris` and their MIME types (if available) and return them as a list of `Pigeon.ImageData`.
3. We'll set up the Pigeon host API in `MainActivity.onCreate` to make it available to the Flutter side.

**On the Flutter side (in `../receive_images_flutter_demo/lib/main.dart`):**

1. The `_ImageReceiverScreenState` will implement the `ImageFlutterApi` (from the generated `pigeon.dart`).
