I've updated your application to receive both single and multiple shared images:

1. Added intent filters in AndroidManifest.xml to receive:
 - Single images with `<action android:name="android.intent.action.SEND">`
 - Multiple images with `<action android:name="android.intent.action.SEND_MULTIPLE">`

2. Updated MainActivity.kt with:
 - Storage for received image URIs using `mutableStateOf`
 - Logic to extract image URIs from both single and multiple image sharing intents
 - A handler for both initial intent and new intents that might come later
 - A simple UI to display the number of received images and their URIs

Now your app can be selected in the share menu when users share images from other apps. When images are shared, your app will receive and display them. This implementation provides the basic structure for handling shared images - you can later enhance it to actually display the images visually rather than just listing their URIs."}]}]}
